{{Infobox language |name=Birifor |nativename= |states=[[Burkina Faso]], [[Ghana]] |ethnicity=[[Birifor people|Birifor]] |speakers={{sigfig|237,310|2}} |date=1993–2003 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Gur languages|Gur]] |fam4=Northern |fam5=[[Oti–Volta languages|Oti–Volta]] |fam6=Moré–Dagbani |fam7=Moré |fam8=Dagaare–Birifor |lc1=bfo|ld1=Malba Birifor (Burkina) |lc2=biv|ld2=Southern Birifor (Ghana) |glotto=biri1257 |glottorefname=Birifor }}
'''Birifor''' is a pair of [[Gur languages]] of [[Burkina Faso]] (Northern Birifor) and [[Ghana]] (Southern Birifor). There are a few thousand speakers of both varieties, which are not mutually intelligible, in [[Ivory Coast]].
