The '''Musa Khel''', or '''Moosa Khel''', is a [[Pashtun tribe]] of [[Gharghasht]] origin. According to [[Horace Arthur Rose]] and the 1911 Encyclopædia Britannica, they are part of the greater [[Kakar]] tribe.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Rose|first1=Harold Arthur|title=Glossary of the Tribes and Castes of the Punjab and North West Frontier Province|date=1911|publisher=Asian Educational Services, India|isbn=978-8120605053|page=438|edition=Facsimile edition 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Musa Khel |volume=19 |page=43}}</ref> The tribe originates from [[Ghazni province]] in [[Afghanistan]] and resides in the tribal range of [[Musakhel District, Pakistan|Musakhel]] and [[Batagram District]] in the [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa|Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa]] province of [[Pakistan]] and Afghanistan. Moosa Khel has the lowest literacy rate in Pakistan&mdash;10.37%&mdash;and is also a sub-tribe to Babozai, which is part of the major [[Pashtuns|Pashtun]] tribe. {{citation needed|date=October 2017}}

